  "title": "rangeSlider should support more formatting functions",
  "body": "The rangeSlider should support formatting for the min/medium/max values, similar to how it formats the tooltip.\r\n\r\nThis is how timestamps look currently:\r\n![Date example](https://i.imgur.com/IHG4xxV.png)\r\n\r\n**Do you want to request a *feature* or report a *bug*?**\r\nFeature\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your use case for such a feature?**\r\nHandling dates.  For example, a facet of timestamps.\r\n\r\n**Feature: What is your proposed API entry? The new option to add? What is the behavior?**\r\nMaybe something like\r\n\r\n```\r\ntemplates: {\r\n   values: function(value) {\r\n       return moment(value, 'X').format('ll');\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWhere values refers to the min, medium, and max values shown under the rangeSlider.\r\n\r\n**What is the version you are using? Always use the latest one before opening a bug issue.**\r\nLatest\r\n",
